listitem.para:
a Unicode UTF-8 text file containing a package description
            (for details of the syntax of this file, see
            )

example.programlisting:
Name: Test1
Version: 0.0.1
Cabal-Version: >= 1.2
License: BSD3
Author:  Jane Doe
Synopsis: Test package to test configurations
Category: Example

Flag Debug {
  Description: Enable debug support
  Default:     False
}

Library {
  Build-Depends:   base
  Exposed-Modules: Testing.Test1
  Extensions:      CPP
  if flag(debug) {
    GHC-Options: -DDEBUG
    if !os(windows) {
      CC-Options: "-DDEBUG"
    } else {
      CC-Options: "-DNDEBUG"
    }
  }
}

listitem.para:
The architecture of the computer being used to build the
		package, eg i386, x86_64,
		ppc or sparc
